import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['time'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Time')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the overall trend of commits made to Github repositories between January 2015 and May 2015?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['count'])
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=range(0, 60, 5), color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Commits')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the number of commits made to Github repositories?')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y/%m/%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['time'])]
    data['day'] = data['time'].dt.date
    data = data.groupby('day').mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['day'], data['count'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['count'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average')
    ax.set_xlabel('Day')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average Commits')
    ax.set_title('What is the average number of commits made to Github repositories per day?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
